ge-id=\"5a29271e0d9297f066130672\" data-type=\"image\" />\n            \n          \n          \n        \n\n        \n\n      \n\n        \n\n        \n          \n            \n              <noscript><img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/59f286aa4c0dbf9244a43d28/1512646489602-PSJ1DZ898EBZV523D5Z1/IMG_1423.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_1423.jpg\" /></noscript><img class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/59f286aa4c0dbf9244a43d28/1512646489602-PSJ1DZ898EBZV523D5Z1/IMG_1423.jpg\" data-image=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/59f286aa4c0dbf9244a43d28/1512646489602-PSJ1DZ898EBZV523D5Z1/IMG_1423.jpg\" data-image-dimensions=\"1500x1000\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" alt=\"IMG_1423.jpg\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5a292734419202965278dbc1\" data-type=\"image\" />\n            \n          \n          \n        \n\n        \n\n      \n    \n  </div>\n\n  \n\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n\n<p>Following their wins at the <a href=\"https://www.thschool.org/news/2017/wsc-world-qualifiers\">World Qualifiers</a> last July,&nbsp;TH School students made the journey to New Haven, Connecticut to compete in the final round of the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.scholarscup.org/\">World Scholar\'s Cup</a>, called the Tournament of Champions, at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.yale.edu/\">Yale University</a>.&nbsp;After four days of competition, six of our Grade 11 and 12 students earned 23 medals and several impressive awards.</p><p>The group with Nguyen Dac Ngoc Mai, Bui Nguyen Phuong Nhu, and Le Hong Thuy earned a silver medal for Debate Champion and a silver medal for Team Debate.</p><p>The group with Bui Lam Tra, Nguyen Tran Khanh Mai, and Nguyen Anh Trung earned a silver medal in the Scholar’s Bowl.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>And Nguyen Anh Trung earned a gold medal for 1st in School, silver medals for Challenge, Debate, Writing, History and Science, and recognition as the Top 17 in Social Studies.</p><p>Our students took advantage of their close proximity to New York City and boarded a train for Grand Central Station to spend some time exploring the Big Apple.</p><p>Congratulations to our champions for representing TH School and Vietnam at the World Scholar\'s Cup!</p>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p><em>Source</em>: <a href=\"http://giaoduc.net.vn/Giao-duc-24h/Hoc-sinh-TH-School-tranh-tai-cung-1000-hoc-gia-nhi-tai-Dai-hoc-Yale-post181537.gd\">Giaoduc</a></p><p> </p>\n\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;', NULL, NULL, 14, 'our-activities', 'Our activities', ',14,', ',our-activities,', NULL, 'WSC Champions', 'world-scholars-cup-finals', 'images/news/original/WSC+New+Haven.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-11-21 10:00:00', '1900-01-20 10:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 57, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0);
INSERT INTO `fs_news` VALUES (781, '<p>Mr. John has worked with students in Years 6, 7, 10, 11 and 12 to produce a colourful and heavily-patterned large-scale painting, titled \"Where Souls Soar in the Air Above Water.\" This week, two panels were installed in the canteen and one panel instal', '&nbsp;\n\n<h2>Secondary art students saturate the walls with a colourful painting</h2><p>Mr. John has worked with students in Years 6, 7, 10, 11 and 12 to produce a colourful and heavily-patterned large-scale painting, titled \"Where Souls Soar in the Air Above Water.\" This week, two panels were installed in the canteen and one panel installed in the library. The following is the statement accompanying the work:</p><blockquote>Students in Years 6, 7, 10 and 11 examined the work of Japanese artist Yayoi Kusama, whose colourful and obsessive patterning reflects her poetic and spiritual vision of infinity. Their research served as the starting point for a multi-panel large-scale painting. They worked collaboratively to paint circular motifs on board and build up layers until every available surface was colonized by pattern. They were challenged to share authorship of each area of interest and to allow the work to progress in new or different directions with each session in the studio. The end result is a hard-fought constellation of circles, colours and patterns that bleeds over the edges of the board.</blockquote><p> </p><p>You can see the students\' work prominently displayed in the Canteen in the secondary block and the Library in the primary block.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n    \n  \n    <div\n        class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-hidden\n          design-layout-inline\n          \n          \n          \n        \"\n        data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"\n    >\n\n      \n\n      \n        <figure\n            class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              intrinsic\n            